# domain-models

## Core Entity Types

1. Workspace Model
```typescript
interface Workspace {
  rootNode: string
  nodes: Node[]
  edges: Edge[]
  domain: DomainType
  templateType: string
  version: number
}
```

2. Node Types
- Root (exactly one per workspace)
- Frontend
- Backend 
- Requirement
- Documentation
- Integration

3. Edge Types
- Depends-on
- Implements
- Contains
- References
- Blocks

## Domain Relationships

1. Domain Ring Structure
- Ring 1: Core Business Logic
- Ring 2: Domain Services
- Ring 3: Technical Implementation
- Ring 4: Infrastructure
- Ring 5: External Systems
- Ring 6: Documentation

2. Template Categories
- Product Requirements
- Technical Architecture
- Integration Specs
- User Stories
- Documentation Cards

## Validation Rules

1. Node Constraints
- Single root node required
- No orphaned nodes allowed
- Maximum depth: 6 levels
- Required fields per type

2. Edge Validation
- No circular dependencies
- Cross-domain rules
- Parent-child type restrictions
- Maximum connections per node: 15

3. Content Rules
- Minimum documentation required
- Link validation
- Required sections by node type
- Maximum content length limits

## Template Structure

1. Card Templates
```typescript
interface CardTemplate {
  sections: Section[]
  requiredFields: string[]
  validationRules: Rule[]
  defaultContent: ContentBlock[]
  domainType: DomainType
}
```

2. Section Types
- Overview
- Requirements
- Technical Details
- Dependencies
- Documentation
- Testing Notes

3. Content Blocks
- Text
- Checklists
- Code Snippets
- Diagrams
- Links
- Attachments

## Workspace Version Control

1. Version Model
```typescript
interface WorkspaceVersion {
  id: string
  parentVersion: string
  changes: Change[]
  metadata: VersionMetadata
  timestamp: Date
}
```

2. Change Tracking
- Node modifications
- Edge updates
- Content changes
- Template updates

